<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6039&amp;p=56445#p56445"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">pivotman wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Do all cart that don't have pads change there mirroring at will?<br /></div><br />Yes. Even some that do have pads, such as <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/TFROM" class="postlink">TFROM</a>, have three sets of pads: "force vertical arrangement", "force horizontal arrangement", and "mapper controlled".<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />What about an mmc1?<br /></div><br />MMC1 is more flexible than a standard MMC3 in mirroring: it can freely switch among vertical mirroring, horizontal mirroring, and AOROM-style single screen mirroring. MMC3 lacks the single screen mode except on boards wired in a <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_118" class="postlink">configuration like TLSROM</a>, where the upper CHR ROM bank bit controls mirroring.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Feb 11, 2010 7:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
