<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6039&amp;p=56444#p56444"><![CDATA[
The MMC1 does have mirroring control, so yeah, the games can select mirroring dynamically.<br /><br />I don't know if all carts that don't have pads have software mirroring control, but I'm pretty sure 99% of the time this is the case.<br /><br />Are you trying to make a repro of a game? If so I guess you might be confused about the mirroring defined on the iNES header, is that it? Well, for mappers that have mirroring control that information has no meaning at all. Don't worry about it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Feb 11, 2010 7:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
