<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mirroring Question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6039&amp;p=56441#p56441"><![CDATA[
If you are making a dev cart out of a cart that has the pads, you can install a switch to select between the two options. Each game will have to use only one type of mirroring the whole time though.<br /><br />Some mappers (such as the MMC3) are able to control the mirroring, which means that there are no pads on the cart and games can change the type of mirroring at will.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Feb 11, 2010 6:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
